# deploy/.env — variables for the TLS (always-on / VM) path.
#
# Copy this file to deploy/.env and fill it in. docker compose auto-loads
# deploy/.env when you run compose from the deploy/ directory, and injects these
# into the Caddy service (see docker-compose.tls.yml + caddy/Caddyfile).
#
#   cp deploy/caddy/.env.example deploy/.env   # then edit
#
# NEVER commit deploy/.env (it may hold real domains/secrets) — it is ignored.

# Public domain for the relay. Clients connect at wss://$RELAY_DOMAIN and the
# media edge is https://$RELAY_DOMAIN/blob-gate. Needs a DNS A-record → host IP.
RELAY_DOMAIN=relay.example.com

# Public domain for the CSS Solid pod. Becomes CSS_BASE_URL (=https://$POD_DOMAIN/).
# Needs its own DNS A-record → host IP.
POD_DOMAIN=pod.example.com

# Let's Encrypt account email (cert-expiry + policy notices land here).
ACME_EMAIL=you@example.com

# ── Optional: relay media edge (Cloudflare R2 / any S3). Uncomment to enable. ──
# Enables full-size media at https://$RELAY_DOMAIN/blob-gate (the relay entrypoint
# builds the S3 bucket + capability gate from these). BLOB_GATE_UPLOADERS is the
# comma-separated allow-list of member SIGNING pubkeys that may upload/grant — the
# same key space the client resolves via circleMemberActors. Empty ⇒ nobody uploads.
# R2_ENDPOINT=https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
# R2_BUCKET=canopy-media
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_REGION=auto
# BLOB_GATE_UPLOADERS=<signing-pubkey>,<signing-pubkey>
#
# LOCAL TESTING without R2: run a MinIO (S3-compatible) and point R2_ENDPOINT at it:
#   docker run -d --name minio -p 9000:9000 -e MINIO_ROOT_USER=k -e MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=secret12345 minio/minio server /data
#   docker run --rm --network host -e MC_HOST_l=http://k:secret12345@localhost:9000 minio/mc mb l/canopy-media
#   then R2_ENDPOINT=http://<host>:9000  R2_REGION=us-east-1  R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=k  R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=secret12345
# The apps/e2e-journeys `media` journey proves the whole path (upload→grant→read→deny) against exactly this.

# ── Optional: push wake (Expo). Uncomment to enable. ──
# PUSH_PROVIDER=expo
# EXPO_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ── Optional: 6d online /manage interface. Set this to your DEVICE's pubKey to
# turn on companion-node management + serve the /manage web at
# https://$RELAY_DOMAIN/manage (owner-paired). Empty ⇒ management OFF, /manage has
# no upstream. This is the ONLY key allowed to manage the node. Get it from your
# device (canopy-chat → your identity), or the node logs print its own host key.
# COMPANION_MANAGE_OWNER_PUBKEY=
